  "body": "the white paper in https://ethereum.org/zh/whitepaper/ say timestamp check mechanism in ethereum is：\r\n**\r\nThe basic block validation algorithm in Ethereum is as follows:\r\n\r\nCheck if the previous block referenced exists and is valid.\r\nCheck that the timestamp of the block is greater than that of the referenced previous block and less than _15 minutes_ into the future\r\n**\r\nhowever ，code in GitHub （https://github.com/ethereum/go-ethereum/blob/32150f8aa9789e4c9aa91a59085011eb692ac8ad/consensus/ethash/consensus.go) say:\r\n**\r\nallowedFutureBlockTimeSeconds = int64(15)  \r\nif header.Time > uint64(unixNow+allowedFutureBlockTimeSeconds) {\r\n\t\t\treturn consensus.ErrF\r\n**\r\none say 15 minutes, another say 15 seconds，which is right？Wish for your reply.",
